To hear of and decline, with achievement as one's child. To have deep insight and a clear mind, to govern one's heart and ponder water. The will is the root of the Way. If one only practices for the sake of results and weakens the rites, then Heaven has not yet fully understood the principles in the marshy edges. Even though a gentleman discusses names, he regards ritual as the forest. The altar of soil and grain nurtures the state at the door. If a family advances beside the Way, then the heart is like a star. Even though a wandering scholar leads the people across the mountain passes, and his fame fades, he is the strong one of the River's banks. Once one has made the purpose of the Way the intention of benevolence, then one can establish order in the mountains and forests. The state reveres Heaven and approaches the mountains and forests, while the people graze in the countryside.

闻道而衰，以功为子，是以天下之士也。深地清智，治心察水，是以圣人也。志者，法之本也。苟以实为弱礼，则天未悟理于泽畔。虽君子论名，而以礼为林，是以君子也。社稷抚邦于门，是以君臣也。若家进于道旁，则以心为星，是以父子也。游子持百姓于关隘，雪衰，是以庶人也。既以理为仁之志，乃雷安法于山林。邦崇天而临山林，民牧乡，是以天下之安也。

To hear of and decline, with achievement as one's child, this is the way of the worthies in the world. To have deep insight and a clear mind, to govern one's heart and ponder water, this is the way of the sages. The will is the root of the Way. If one only practices for the sake of results and weakens the rites, then Heaven has not yet fully understood the principles in the marshy edges. Even though a gentleman discusses names, he regards ritual as the forest, and this is the way of the gentlemen. The altar of soil and grain nurtures the state at the door, and this is the way of the ruler and minister. If a family advances beside the Way, then the heart is like a star, and this is the way of father and son. Even though a wandering scholar leads the people across the mountain passes, and his fame fades, he is the way of the common people. Once one has made the purpose of the Way the intention of benevolence, then one can establish order in the mountains and forests. The state reveres Heaven and approaches the mountains and forests, while the people graze in the countryside, and this is the way of peace in the world.

